cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with learning in Stackelberg Security Games, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). The paper also extensively uses machine learning tools to learn and predict adversary behavior (cs.AI). The paper deals with security and crime prevention (cs.CR) and uses theoretical analysis to provide utility guarantees (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with practical questions such as how much data is needed to improve an adversary model's accuracy (cs.SI).
